Build the Nth constructor function for a
Scott-encoded algebraic data type.

A type descriptor is a Scott list of constructor specs.
Each spec is a Scott list of fields.
Each field (Œªx.x) marks a recursive position.
In Haskell notation:
  data Bit  = O | I             is [[],[]]
  data Nat  = Z | S Nat         is [[],[‚ä§]]
  data Bin  = E | O Bin | I Bin is [[],[‚ä§],[‚ä§]]
  data Pair = A | B Pair Pair   is [[],[‚ä§,‚ä§]]
